LAGOS – At least 10 members of the Trade Union Congress of Nigeria (TUC) have petitioned the Inspector General of Police (IGP) over the plan by the union to go ahead with the 12th Triennial Delegates’ Conference despite the subsisting order of the National Industrial Court Lagos. The aggrieved members in a petition dated July 15, 2022, signed by Timothy Oreofe Adewale of Adewale & Adewale, its solicitors also copied the Vice President of Nigeria, Minister of Labour and Employment, Director-General, Department of State Services and the Registrar of Trade. The petitioner said that the court had already restrained congress from going ahead with the election, stressing that any conduct contrary to that is flagrant disobedience to the court. The two days triennial delegates’ conference is scheduled to commence Tuesday, July 19 and 20, 2022. The complainants are; the Association of Senior Staff of Banks, Insurance and Financial Institutions (ASSBIFI). Pulp Paper and Paper Products Printing and Publishing Senior Staff Association of Nigeria (PPAPPPAPSSAN), Nigeria Merchant Navy Officers and Water Transport Senior Staff Association (NMNO/WTSSA), Senior Staff Association of Shipping Clearing and Forwarding Agencies and Air Transport Services Senior Staff Association of Nigeria (ATSSSAN).